{"article_id":"axbE1rNhBEjIR5A9","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"President Trump on Friday became the first president","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"to speak in person at the anti-abortion March for Life rally ,","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"on the heels of a new poll","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"registering record-high dissatisfaction with U.S. abortion laws .","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"\" Unborn children have never had a stronger defender in the White House , \"","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"Trump said in a speech .","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"\" And","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"as the Bible tells us ,","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"each person is wonderfully made . \"","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"He went on to slam Democrats","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"for embracing \" the most radical and extreme positions \"","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"and backing \" taxpayer-funded abortion , all the way up until the moment of birth. \"","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"( Critics say","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"that such procedures do not occur . )","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"The March for Life says","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"its mission is to \" promote the beauty and dignity of every human life","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"by working","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"to end abortion. \"","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"Trump previously spoke at the rally remotely ,","depth":6},{"id":19,"text":"while Vice President Mike Pence in 2017 became the first U.S. vice president","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"to attend .","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"March for Life president Jeanne Mancini applauded the Trump administration in a statement earlier in the week ,","depth":5},{"id":22,"text":"noting","depth":6},{"id":23,"text":"that the administration had appointed anti-abortion judges and federal workers ,","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"cut taxpayer funding for abortions","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"and called for an end to late-term abortions .","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"\" President Trump and his Administration have been consistent champions for life","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"and their support for the March for Life has been unwavering , \"","depth":6},{"id":28,"text":"she said .","depth":5},{"id":29,"text":"The results of a new Gallup poll","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"released Wednesday","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"suggested","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"that discontent over U.S. abortion policy was at an all-time high","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"( 58 % )","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"and satisfaction was at an all-time low","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"( 32 % ) .","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"The survey of more than 1,000 adults ,","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"conducted earlier this month ,","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"tracked an upward trend in those","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"who wanted abortion policy to be less restrictive .","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"Traditionally ,","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"Gallup said ,","depth":12},{"id":42,"text":"most people","depth":13},{"id":43,"text":"dissatisfied with abortion policy","depth":13},{"id":44,"text":"wanted stricter laws","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"- but since 2017 , the year","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"Trump took office ,","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"the share of respondents","depth":13},{"id":48,"text":"desiring less-strict abortion policy","depth":13},{"id":49,"text":"has risen .","depth":12},{"id":50,"text":"Now , \" roughly equal percentages of U.S. adults now are dissatisfied","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"and favor less strict laws","depth":13},{"id":52,"text":"( 22 % )","depth":13},{"id":53,"text":"as are dissatisfied","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"and want stricter laws","depth":13},{"id":55,"text":"( 24 % ) , \"","depth":13},{"id":56,"text":"the report ' s authors said .","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"Mounting support","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"for easing abortion policy","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"was fueled by a rise in Democrats and independents","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"expressing such sentiments over the last 10 years ,","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"the survey found .","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"A flurry of states last year enacted restrictive anti-abortion laws ,","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"including a handful","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"that banned abortion past a certain point in a pregnancy ,","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"and Alabama ,","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"which effectively outlawed abortion in most cases .","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"Many of these laws have been blocked in court from taking effect .","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"The Supreme Court will also hear arguments this year on June Medical Services v. Gee ,","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"which involves a Louisiana law","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"requiring abortion providers to have admitting privileges at a local hospital .","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"The court previously struck down a similar provision in Texas in 2016 ' s Whole Woman ' s Health v. Hellerstedt .","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"\" Americans have grown increasingly dissatisfied with the nation ' s abortion policies since 2017 ,","depth":7},{"id":73,"text":"largely reflecting Democrats '","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"- and to a lesser extent , independents ' -","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"mounting view under Trump","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"that the laws are too strict , \"","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"wrote the authors of the Gallup report .","depth":6},{"id":78,"text":"\" While this may partly be a reaction to Trump ' s rhetoric on the issue ,","depth":6},{"id":79,"text":"it also aligns with an increase in abortion restrictions . \"","depth":6},{"id":80,"text":"A separate poll","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"published Wednesday by the Kaiser Family Foundation","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"found","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"that 59 % of Americans believe","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"abortion should be legal in most","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"( 32 % )","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"or all","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"( 27 % )","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"cases ,","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"while just 11 % thought","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"the procedure should be illegal in all cases .","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"Nearly seven in 10 respondents said","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"they didn ' t want the landmark Supreme Court ruling Roe v. Wade ,","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"which affirmed the right","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"to have an abortion ,","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"to be overturned .","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"Democrats and independents were most likely to express that opinion ,","depth":8},{"id":97,"text":"while a majority of Republicans","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"( 57 % )","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"said","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"they wanted Roe overturned .","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"But many respondents also backed some state abortion restrictions ,","depth":8},{"id":102,"text":"including 69 %","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"who endorsed policies","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"requiring the procedure be performed only by doctors with hospital-admitting privileges ,","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"66 %","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"who supported 24-hour waiting periods between consultation with a provider and the procedure ,","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"and 57 %","depth":11},{"id":108,"text":"who supported a requirement","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"that doctors show and describe ultrasound images to abortion seekers .","depth":12},{"id":110,"text":"Still , criminalizing abortion","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"( that is , through fines or prison time )","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"for providers and abortion-seekers proved unpopular .","depth":8},{"id":113,"text":"A NPR/PBS News/Marist poll of 944 U.S. adults","depth":7},{"id":114,"text":"released in June 2019","depth":7},{"id":115,"text":"echoed those results ,","depth":6},{"id":116,"text":"showing","depth":7},{"id":117,"text":"that 77 % of Americans wanted to keep Roe v. Wade in place ,","depth":8},{"id":118,"text":"but many still wanted additional abortion restrictions or policy changes .","depth":8},{"id":119,"text":"Among the more than three-quarters of Americans","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"who broadly supported Roe ,","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"26 % wanted the Supreme Court to keep it","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"but add more restrictions ,","depth":11},{"id":123,"text":"and 14 % supported keeping it","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"but reducing some restrictions ,","depth":10},{"id":125,"text":"according to that poll .","depth":8},{"id":126,"text":"Some 21 % wanted to see Roe expanded","depth":9},{"id":127,"text":"to secure abortion rights under any circumstance ,","depth":9},{"id":128,"text":"while 16 % wanted to keep it the way it is .","depth":8},{"id":129,"text":"This story was originally published Jan. 23 , 2020 ,","depth":2},{"id":130,"text":"and has been updated .","depth":2}],"relations":[{"parent":261,"left":259,"right":260,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":259,"left":159,"right":258,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":159,"left":151,"right":158,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":151,"left":144,"right":150,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":144,"left":134,"right":143,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":134,"left":132,"right":133,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":132,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":133,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":143,"left":138,"right":142,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":138,"left":135,"right":137,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":135,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":137,"left":6,"right":136,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":136,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":142,"left":9,"right":141,"r